item.dc:creator: @exps35 exps35
item.description:
@exps35 wrote:

IPT gave me around 1.2 mb/s yesterday. It was pwn.

Another benefit of private communities is that people understand the importance of being a respectful member, and if any of their underlings (invited people) mess up, they are at blame.
Also, it is much easier for moderators to keep the files clean, resulting in less malware.
Most of the time, there is only 1 result for a torrent, and everybody is seeding it, whereas on PirateBay there would be 10 different torrents of the same album, each with only 10 seeders.
